    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for hwloc is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP2.",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "hwloc provides command line tools and a C API to obtain the hierarchical map of key computing elements, such as: NUMA memory nodes, shared caches, processor sockets, processor cores, and processor \"threads\". hwloc also gathers various attributes such as cache and memory information, and is portable across a variety of different operating systems and platforms.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nAn issue was discovered in open-mpi hwloc 2.1.0 allows attackers to cause a denial of service or other unspecified impacts via glibc-cpuset in topology-linux.c.(CVE-2022-47022)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for hwloc is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP2.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of critical. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Critical",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
